I think we have time for, like, one or two

00:18:01.319 --> 00:18:05.319
Are there any situations where you would suggest that someone start a new project and still use the link?

00:18:27.319 --> 00:18:28.319
No, it's a short answer

00:18:31.319 --> 00:18:32.319
I think we can use this

00:18:32.319 --> 00:18:35.319
So, one more question here

00:18:38.319 --> 00:18:41.319
Will it work with Vetiver? And if so, when?

00:18:45.319 --> 00:18:46.319
Maybe

00:18:46.319 --> 00:18:48.319
No, this is not something I have dived into yet

00:18:48.319 --> 00:18:51.319
This is certainly something that we will look into

00:18:55.319 --> 00:18:57.319
It should work with Connect now

00:18:57.319 --> 00:19:00.319
It should, of course, integrate well with all our other projects

00:19:00.319 --> 00:19:03.319
But it is still early days

00:19:03.319 --> 00:19:06.319
So, I would not try to use Vetiver with it yet

00:19:06.319 --> 00:19:08.319
But it will come, of course

00:19:10.319 --> 00:19:12.319
I think we can get one quick one in

00:19:12.319 --> 00:19:15.319
So, why Plumber 2?

00:19:15.319 --> 00:19:17.319
I think you touched on this a little bit in your talk

00:19:17.319 --> 00:19:20.319
But why Plumber 2 and not overwrite Plumber with the new code

00:19:20.319 --> 00:19:25.319
And require legacy users to install a legacy version of the package?

00:19:28.319 --> 00:19:30.319
So, some of it comes back to

00:19:32.319 --> 00:19:34.319
Like this slide

00:19:34.319 --> 00:19:35.319
It will stay on CRAN

00:19:35.319 --> 00:19:38.319
You don't have to do anything with the thing that you put in production

00:19:38.319 --> 00:19:41.319
I think it's nicer of me to not break anything

00:19:41.319 --> 00:19:45.319
And require users to do something for their business logic

00:19:45.319 --> 00:19:47.319
So, I'd rather start afresh

00:19:47.319 --> 00:19:50.319
And allow users to just continue as before

00:19:50.319 --> 00:19:54.319
But be excited enough to kind of change what they're doing gradually

00:19:54.319 --> 00:19:57.319
So, I think that is the main thing, really

00:19:57.319 --> 00:20:03.319
And people should be able to live with having a 2 after it

00:20:03.319 --> 00:20:05.319
It worked well enough with ggplot2

00:20:05.319 --> 00:20:07.319
